"title": "7708: apostles, function of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7708",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In the NT apostles are servants, first of Jesus Christ and then of the church. Apostolic service embraces a wide range of specific functions.</p>\n<h2>The functions of apostles during the earthly life and ministry of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Being with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14\">MRK 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:1\">MAT 17:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:30-Mark6:32\">MRK 6:30–6:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:10\">LUK 9:10</a></p>\n<h3>Learning from Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:1-Matt18:4\">MAT 18:1–18:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:10-Mark4:12\">MRK 4:10–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:2\">ACT 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Being sent out on a mission by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1-Luke9:6\">LUK 9:1–9:6</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:5-Matt10:10\">MAT 10:5–10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:7-Mark6:13\">MRK 6:7–6:13</a> <em>As Jesus Christ's representatives their ministry was an extension of his.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14-Mark3:15\">MRK 3:14–3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Being commissioned to witness to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:39\">ACT 10:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:18–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:15\">MRK 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:46-Luke24:49\">LUK 24:46–24:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:18\">JHN 17:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:21\">JHN 20:21</a></p>\n<h2>Apostles in the early church</h2>\n<h3>They were witnesses of the resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21-Acts1:22\">ACT 1:21–1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:32\">ACT 2:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:15\">ACT 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:33\">ACT 4:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:31\">ACT 13:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1\">1PE 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>They were servants of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:1\">2PE 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:1\">1CO 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:23\">2CO 11:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:1\">PHP 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:1\">TIT 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>They were servants of the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:4\">2CO 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:25\">ROM 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:5\">2CO 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:8\">2CO 11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1-1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:1–5:3</a></p>\n<h3>They were the foundations of the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:20\">EPH 2:20</a></strong> <em>Probably a reference to the apostolic preaching. The absence of the article before “prophets” suggests that “the apostles and prophets” represents one group of people, not two.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:9\">GAL 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:17\">JUD 1:17</a> <em>the prophetic ministry of the apostles</em></p>\n<h3>They preached the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1-Rom1:5\">ROM 1:1–1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:20\">MRK 16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:19-Rom15:20\">ROM 15:19–15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17\">1CO 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15-Gal1:16\">GAL 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>They were guardians and teachers of the truth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13-John16:15\">JHN 16:13–16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2\">ACT 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:2-Eph3:6\">EPH 3:2–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:15\">2TH 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:11\">2TI 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>They founded churches</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:1-1Cor9:2\">1CO 9:1–9:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:5-1Cor3:6\">1CO 3:5–3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:10\">1CO 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>They were authority figures within the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2-Acts6:6\">ACT 6:2–6:6</a> <em>The apostles took the initiative. Whilst they did not themselves appoint the Seven, they confirmed their appointment.</em></p>\n<h3>They were called to suffer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:11-2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:11–1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:18\">ACT 5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:9\">1CO 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:23-2Cor11:29\">2CO 11:23–11:29</a></p>\n<h3>They were empowered by the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:8\">ACT 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:22\">JHN 20:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">ACT 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:4-Eph3:5\">EPH 3:4–3:5</a></p>\n<h3>They were able to bestow the Spirit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:14-Acts8:18\">ACT 8:14–8:18</a> <em>Peter and John officially induct Samaritans as members of the body of Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:6\">ACT 19:6</a></p>",
